      It was cold. Hospital clothes were clearly not designed for any long stay in premises without heating, not to mention the February streets. The first breeze of the dank winter wind made Taylor realize this with all its might.
      She wasn't too picky, setting up the Bai-Hu coordinates to move, which is why she found herself, along with Persona, right on one of the streets of the long deserted part of the Docks.
      Away from the conflict, the Defender took his usual form, allowing him to move around the neighborhood without much trouble and without fear of being noticed because of the huge size of the Person.
      By breaking the barn lock on one of the doors, she managed to get inside the most decent warehouse. Inside, there was a darkness interrupted by the rare rays of light that fell from a few windows, illuminating small areas of space. It was foolish to hope for electricity in this part of the city, at least.
      But even the loneliness and roof over one's head, which was so desirable, did not solve all the problems. More precisely... they didn't solve anything. And now she clearly understood that. Yes, she was healthy. Physically. But she didn't even have banal clothes, let alone money. Hell, even underwear wasn't there! And the worst part was that Taylor couldn't remember the last time she ate seriously. Everything was a little bit difficult with hospital food, as they fed it three times and something like liquid porridge, which practically didn't give it any nutritional value.
      Getting money and food in this part of town was a very difficult task. However, as in any other part of the city. Taylor doubted that anyone in their right mind would want to sell something or lend clothes to a barefoot girl in a hospital gown alone for a naked body. To meet with the police or the SKP... Taylor had no desire.
      Closer to the warm skin of Bai-hoo, she tried to warm herself up and think about what had happened soberly.... As far as possible in her case.
      Sophia...
      Emma. Madison. Soph...
      "Not now"! - She shouted at herself with a huge effort of will to keep the memories of that day away from her.
